{
  "profile_id": "client-edge-not-anxious-001",
  "coach_config_id": "coach-v5a-guided-walk-haiku",
  "turns": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "Yeah, so — I'm not really sure this is the right venue for it, but people keep suggesting I talk to someone. The thing is, I keep putting off this product launch. Big one. And I genuinely can't figure out why, because fear isn't really my deal — I mean, I free solo, I've taken companies through some pretty high-stakes moments — so it's not that. It's more like a... logistical thing, maybe. Or discipline. I don't know."
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "What would happen if you launched it tomorrow?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "*slight pause, thinking it through*\n\nProbably fine. I mean, it's ready enough. There'd be some scrambling on the backend but... we'd handle it. We always do.\n\n*small smile*\n\nHonestly the launch going badly isn't really what's stopping me. I've had things not go well before and it's — you just course-correct. That's part of it. So it's not like I'm sitting here dreading some outcome. It's more like I just... keep finding other things to do. Which is annoying, more than anything."
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "What's the thing you keep finding to do instead?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "*small laugh*\n\nHonestly? Dumb stuff. I'll check email. Go for a run — which at least is useful. Sometimes I'll just start working on something completely unrelated, like I'll get deep into some operational thing that didn't need my attention that day. \n\nAnd then I'll look up and it's 4pm and I haven't touched the launch materials.\n\nIt's not like I'm paralyzed or anything. I'm productive. Just... not on that. Which is why I figured it was more of a focus thing, or maybe I just need a better system. Someone suggested a coach, so — here I am."
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "You called it \"dumb stuff\" — what's dumb about it?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "*brief pause*\n\nI guess because it doesn't need to be me doing it. Like, the operational stuff — I have people for that. I know that. And yet I'm the one who ends up in the weeds on it.\n\n*slight tilt of the head*\n\nIt's not even that I enjoy it more. It's just... easier to start, maybe. The launch has more moving pieces, so maybe it's just a complexity thing. Like my brain defaults to the simpler task.\n\nThat's probably it, actually. It's not emotional, it's just — task switching is hard when something has a lot of dependencies. I've read about that. ADHD stuff, kind of, even though I've never been diagnosed."
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "You landed on an explanation pretty fast there.\n\nWhat were you feeling just before you grabbed it?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 9,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "*small smile, slight pause*\n\nHm.\n\n*looks off for a moment, then back*\n\nI mean... nothing, really. I was just thinking through it. It felt like I was describing it accurately — like that's what happens. The simpler task is easier to start.\n\n*beat*\n\nI don't know that I was feeling anything in particular. I was just... answering the question."
    },
    {
      "turn": 10,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "What's it like to sit with not knowing why?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 11,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "*small shrug, even tone*\n\nIt's fine. A little frustrating maybe, in a practical sense — like, I want to solve it, so not having a clear answer is mildly annoying. But it's not like it's keeping me up at night.\n\n*pause*\n\nI'm pretty comfortable with uncertainty in general. That's kind of a prerequisite for what I do. You're never going to have full information, so you get okay with that early on or you don't last.\n\n*settles back slightly*\n\nSo sitting with not knowing is... fine. It's just a problem I haven't solved yet."
    },
    {
      "turn": 12,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "\"Just a problem I haven't solved yet.\"\n\nWhat if it's not a problem?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 13,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "*slight tilt of the head, considering*\n\nWhat do you mean?\n\n*pause*\n\nLike... it's not worth solving? Or that framing it as a problem is the wrong frame?\n\n*small smile*\n\nI'm open to that. I just — I'm not sure what else it would be. Something's getting in the way of something I want to do. That seems like a problem by definition.\n\n*beat, genuine curiosity but still very even*\n\nWhat are you thinking?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 14,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "I'm not thinking anything yet. I'm curious what it's like when you're not solving it — not managing it, not framing it. Just... the launch sitting there undone."
    }
  ],
